The following experiment shows that vectors are also saved contiguously in memory, same as array:

vector<int> vec = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
int n = vec.size();

for(int *p = &vec[0]; p < &vec[n]; ++p) cout << *p << " ";
cout << endl;

Output: 1 2 3 4 5

